  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user, I always want to see what I'm typing.\n\n### Description\n\n*Type*: Bug\n\n*Summary*: when replying snippet is ~5 rows (max) and you typing a reply in message box - you can't see what you are typing starting from 3d lin on Android (LG V20) and from 8d line on IOS (IPhone 7).\nThis issue is reproducible on nightly 01/04/2018 (so it is not caused by https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/7666) but it is not on release 0.11.0 (tested on IOS 12, iPhone XS)\n\n#### Expected behavior\nmessage area is scrollable, can see last row\n\n#### Actual behavior\n![photo_2019-04-02 15 08 21 jpeg 2019-04-02 15-08-43](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/55404972-66673180-5559-11e9-8f3e-96b571c590fa.png)\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status\n- Open any chat\n- Send long message (>5 rows)\n- Long tap on message\n- On message input type > 3 rows for Android (>8 rows for IOS)\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n* Status version: nightly 01/04/2018 \n* Operating System: Android, IOS",
